The '''Botswana–Harvard AIDS Institute Partnership''' (BHP) is an [[HIV/AIDS research]] and training organization. It was established in 1996.<ref>http://www.hsph.harvard.edu/bhp/about_us/index.html Botswana–Harvard AIDS Institute website, "About us", retrieved April 28, 2011.</ref> It is a partnership between the [[Politics of Botswana|Government of Botswana]] and the [[Harvard AIDS Initiative]]. Its goal is to further HIV/AIDS research.

