''' Ramón Villeda Bermúdez''' (10 May 1937, [[Santa Rosa de Copán]] – 20 July 2012) was a Honduran veterinarian and [[Liberal Party (Honduras)|Liberal Party]] politician.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elheraldo.hn/csp/mediapool/sites/ElHeraldo/Pais/story.csp?cid=570889&sid=299&fid=214 |title=Muere Ramón Villeda Bermúdez |publisher=''El Heraldo''|accessdate=23 May 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name="FunesV.2000">{{cite book|last=Funes|first=Matías|title=Los deliberantes: el poder militar en Honduras|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WvO6DXs7NMEC&pg=PA198|year=2000|publisher=Editorial Guaymuras|language=Spanish|isbn=978-99926-15-52-2|page=198}}</ref> He has held several important positions in administration, including President of the [[Banco Nacional de Desarrollo Agrícola]] (1998-2000) and Vice President of the [[Congreso Nacional de Honduras]] (2004-2005) and President of the [[Banco Central de Honduras]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ccichonduras.org/website/descargas/presentaciones/2014/PROGRAMA_MONETARIO_2010_2011.PDF|title=Programa Montetario 2010-2011|publisher=Ccichonduras.org|accessdate=23 May 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304044753/http://www.ccichonduras.org/website/descargas/presentaciones/2014/PROGRAMA_MONETARIO_2010_2011.PDF|archivedate=4 March 2016|df=}}</ref> from 2010 until his death in 2012.
