'''Timothy Frances Cloughesy''' is a Clinical Professor and Director of the Neuro-Oncology Program at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]].<ref name="ucla">{{cite web|title=Timothy Cloughesy M.D.|url=http://www.neurooncology.ucla.edu/Research/TimothyCloughesy.aspx|website=[[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]] Neuro-Oncology|accessdate=10 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=GREAT READ BRAIN CANCER TAKES A TOLL, BUT UNLOCKS HER CREATIVITY|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/great-reads/la-me-c1-brain-cancer-poet-20150114-story.html|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=10 January 2018}}</ref> He is an expert on the treatment of [[brain cancer]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1998/may/06/news/mn-46795 |title=Cancer Drugs Face Long Road From Mice to Men |last=Cimons |first=Marlene |date=1998-05-06 |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=2018-07-08 |last2=GETLIN |first2=JOSH |language=en-US |issn=0458-3035 |last3=II |first3=THOMAS H. MAUGH}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Kaufman |first=Judi |date=March 2002 |title=Art of the Brain UCLA Neuro-Oncology Program |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1550327/ |journal=Neoplasia (New York, N.Y.) |volume=4 |issue=2 |pages=181–183 |issn=1522-8002 |pmc=1550327}}</ref>

He completed his [[Doctor of Medicine|MD]] at [[Tulane University School of Medicine]] in 1987.<ref name="ucla"/> He has an [[h-index]] of 93.<ref>{{cite web|title=Timothy Cloughesy|url=https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=6-vSif8AAAAJ&hl=en&oi=sra|website=[[Google Scholar]]|accessdate=10 January 2018}}</ref>

